## Wallace Line and Other Faunal Boundaries — JRF Favourite

These transitional lines are extremely high-yield for competitive exams.**Wallace Line (1859):** Passes between Bali and Lombok (Indonesia), and between Borneo and Sulawesi. West = Asian species. East = Australian/mixed. Named after Alfred Russel Wallace who first noticed it.

**Weber Line:** Lies east of the Wallace Line. The point where the number of Australian species first exceeds the number of Asian species. Named after German biologist Max Weber.

**Lydekker Line:** The eastern boundary of Wallacea. East of this line, the fauna is almost entirely Australian. Named after British geologist Richard Lydekker.

**Wallacea:** The transition zone between the Wallace Line and Lydekker Line — a mixing zone of Asian and Australian species found on islands like Sulawesi, Lombok, Flores, Timor, and the Maluku islands. Sulawesi has many unique endemic species found nowhere else.

